definition: to unload/to unhitch/to remove or strip/to get rid of

sentences.english: You can see the second platter and the second dumper.

sentences.english: However the hydraulic drive system and the control system have important influence on the performance of the self-loading and unloading vehicle.

sentences.english: This is a Curious George and the Dump Truck Book.
